cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.LO, cs.DM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with maintaining a database and updating it with First-Order queries, which falls under the scope of data structures. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity class DynFO+ and its ability to decide isomorphism of Planar 3-connected graphs, which is a topic related to computational complexity. 
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with isomorphism of Planar 3-connected graphs, which is a topic related to computational geometry. 
4. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper extensively uses First-Order Logic to maintain and update the database, which falls under the scope of logic in computer science. 
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with graph isomorphism and canonical descriptions of graphs, which are topics related to discrete mathematics.
